The paper introduces a new approximate solution technique for first-order Markov decision processes (FOMDPs) using linear programming. This technique is applicable to a wide range of domains and allows for determining bounds on approximation error. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with decision-making and optimization problems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves learning the weights of the linear value function. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes a new algorithmic technique for solving FOMDPs. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) as it can be applied to decision-making problems involving multiple agents. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) as it can be used for optimizing the behavior of robots in various scenarios.
